<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Smok'n Latern Wins Haughton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) --Smok'n Lantern enjoyed a  
near-perfect trip and then held off a late bid by Credit Winner to 
win the $509,400 Peter Haughton Memorial at the Meadowlands on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Haughton, a one-mile trot for two-year-old colts and  
geldings, showcases some of the nation's best juvenile trotters. 
</P>
<P>
	Driven by Berndt Lindstedt and trained by Jan Johnson, Smok'n  
Lantern got an enviable trip taking cover behind Brad's Photo, who 
led the pack through fractions of 29 2/5, 58 3/5 and 1:28 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
	At the top of the stretch, Smok'n Lantern, who has been on the  
board with three wins and a second place in all three of his stakes 
starts, finally overtook the tiring Brads Photo and then held off a 
late drive by Credit Winner to win by length and a quarter in 1:58 
3/5. 
</P>
<P>
	The son of Pine Chip paid $9.40, 4.60 and 2.80, while Credit  
Winner took second and Brendt Hanover overcame an early break to 
finish third. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, unheralded longshot Dream of Joy captured the  
$484,800 Merrie Annabelle trot for two-year old fillies, overtaking 
Marita's Victory with a burst of late speed down the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	Dream of Joy, the Swedish-owned daughter of Victory Dream, was  
driven by little-known Jim Meittinis and trained by Per Eriksson. 
Racing for just the fourth time overall and the second time in a 
stakes race, Dream of Joy went off at 17-1 and paid $36.40, 11.80 
and 6.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Dream of Joy edged Marita's Victory by a length and a quarter at  
the wire in 1:58 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
	In the $461,400 Sweetheart Pace for two-year-old fillies,  
Panything Goes came flying down the stretch from off the pace to 
win a four-horse photo finish in 1:54 3/5. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
