<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 02:30:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Says He Hasn't Taken Andro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire is hitting home runs in bunches  
again, and without androstenedione giving him a controversial 
boost. 
</P>
<P>
	Hours before he hit career home run No. 499 and his 42nd of the  
season to tie Sammy Sosa for the major league lead, the St. Louis 
Cardinals' slugger disclosed Wednesday that he hasn't taken the 
over-the-counter dietary supplement for four months. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire revealed his decision about a year after his use of  
andro became public. That disclosure prompted widespread criticism 
and some speculation that his 70-homer season was tainted. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire's reasoning: He did it for the kids.  
</P>
<P>
	``I thought long and hard about it and I don't like the way it  
was portrayed like I was the endorser of the product, which I 
wasn't,'' McGwire said. ``I don't like how it's portrayed, but 
young kids take it because of me. I don't like that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire knows he's a role model, and that was perhaps the  
biggest reason for his decision. 
</P>
<P>
	``I discourage young people from taking it,'' he said. ``If  
you're old enough and you have your own mind, you can do whatever 
you want.'' 
</P>
<P>
	NL president Len Coleman praised McGwire's decision.  
</P>
<P>
	``Mark's focus is on contributions to society,'' Coleman said.  
``He leads by example. The youth of the world are well served by 
Mark's value structure.'' 
</P>
<P>
	After the game, McGwire refused to address the subject.  
</P>
<P>
	``Let's not talk about that,'' he said. ``Come on, I said what I  
said before the game and that's all I'm going to comment on it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Manager Tony La Russa and teammates felt a sense of validation  
to McGwire's 42 homers this season and to his 70-homer season. 
</P>
<P>
	``That is such a ridiculous part of the McGwire story,'' La  
Russa said angrily. ``He's at 499 and what's andro do with it?'' 
</P>
<P>
	Injured outfielder Eric Davis said McGwire's performance should  
quiet the critics. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know too much about it, but if he says he's off it and  
he's got 42 homers, what's that say?'' Davis said. ``He hit 49 his 
rookie year, when testosterone probably wasn't even available. Give 
the man a break.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Padres didn't want to touch the subject.  
</P>
<P>
	``I don't have any reaction,'' manager Bruce Bochy said.  
``That's his personal business.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Closer Trevor Hoffman said he didn't know anything about the  
subject, and outfielder John Vander Wal said simply: ``It's up to 
him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Androstenedione is metabolized into testosterone, which is  
considered a steroid. It is banned by the Olympics, the NCAA, the 
NFL, and the men's and women's tennis tours, though it is permitted 
in baseball. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire's admission that he used andro sparked a tenfold  
increase in sales of the supplement last fall, much of it through 
the Internet, and led many steroid experts to warn of serious 
health consequences for teen-agers who take it to emulate McGwire. 
</P>
<P>
	Major league baseball has commissioned a study of andro by  
Harvard scientists. No decision is expected until later this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's in process. They're working on it,'' commissioner Bud  
Selig said Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Last August, McGwire acknowledged to The Associated Press that  
he had used andro for more than a year. Colorado's Dante Bichette 
was among a group of other players who said they took it. 
</P>
<P>
	As spring training opened this year, McGwire said andro was  
legal and that it had ``absolutely nothing to do with me hitting a 
baseball.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He said then he took it to get through late-season workouts.  
</P>
<P>
	``I don't endorse the product and I never did,'' he said then.  
``Someone stuck their nose in my locker.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire's recent statistics appear to show that he's fine  
without andro. Including Wednesday's shot, he has homered 15 times 
in 20 games. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
