<HEADLINE> Clinton Nominates 6 to Federal Bench </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton named six nominees to the  
federal bench on Thursday, including two for the Eastern District 
of Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton named attorney David M. Lawson of Troy and Marianne O.  
Battani, a Wayne County Circuit Court judge from Gross Pointe 
Woods, to judgeships in Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	Steven D. Bell of Akron, Ohio, a partner with Ulmer &AMP; Berne, was  
named to the bench in the Northern District of Ohio; Ronald A. 
Guzman, a U.S. magistrate from LaGrange Park, Ill., was nominated 
to serve in the Northern District of Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
	Ann Claire Williams, a federal judge in Chicago since 1985, was  
named to the U.S. Seventh Circuit Court of Appeals, and James A. 
Wynn Jr., an associate judge on the North Carolina Court of 
Appeals, was named to the U.S. Fourth Circuit Court of Appeals. 
</P>
<P>
	All nominations are subject to Senate confirmation.  
  	   	
</P>
