<HEADLINE> Cincinnati Reds Promote Buddy Bell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Former Cincinnati Reds third baseman Buddy  
Bell was promoted to director of player development today. 
</P>
<P>
	The job opened up when Muzzy Jackson resigned to become an  
assistant general manager with the Kansas City Royals. Jackson 
spent five years in the Royals' organization before serving as the 
Reds' player development director for the last two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Bell rejoined the Reds last September as minor league field  
coordinator after three seasons managing the Detroit Tigers. He 
recently managed the United States to the silver medal in the Pan 
Am Games, earning a berth in next year's Olympic baseball 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Bill Doran, who was Bell's assistant, was promoted to minor  
league field coordinator. 
  	   	
</P>
