<HEADLINE> Temple Extends Chaney's Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Temple extended the contract of basketball  
coach John Chaney through the 2002 season, the school announced 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Coach Chaney exhibits both on and off the court the ideals of  
Temple University. As a great teacher and someone with 
unquestionable character, he is an inspirational leader for our 
student-athletes and sports fans across the country,'' Temple 
athletic director Dave O'Brien said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Chaney, who has coached at Temple since 1982, has a 380-160  
record with the Owls, the best in the school's history. Overall, 
Chaney has a 605-219 record in 27 years of college coaching. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, Chaney led the Owls to a 24-11 record, the Atlantic  
10 East Division championship and a trip to the NCAA tournament. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
