<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nike Tournament On Despite Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT SMITH, Ark. (AP) -- Hot weather that harmed greens at  
Hardscrabble Country Club did not do enough damage to cause a delay 
in the Nike Fort Smith Classic golf tournament, organizers said. 
</P>
<P>
	The tournament will begin Aug. 16 as scheduled.  
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, tournament director Ben Gosey said at least four  
greens had been damaged and that the tournament could be moved to 
mid-October. The Oct. 11-17 date would have attracted a great deal 
of attention because that is one week before the top 50 money 
winners get together for the Nike Tour Championship. After that 
tournament, the top 15 money winners get PGA tour cards. 
</P>
<P>
	Gosey said that PGA officials decided Wednesday that the  
Hardscrabble greens were acceptable for tournament play. He had 
said earlier that the greens had been hurt by recent hot weather 
and a watering system with too much silt. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're trying to get all of our suppliers lined back up because  
we had put everything on hold,'' Gosey said. 
</P>
<P>
	Gosey said tour agronomist Tom Brown visited Hardscrabble last  
week and recommended the event be postponed. Gosey said he received 
a call Monday from Dale Antram of the PGA who said players at the 
Nike event in Omaha, Neb., would be advised of the move to October. 
</P>
<P>
	Gosey said members of the Hardscrabble Board of Directors and  
several major sponsors met Wednesday to discuss the possible 
postponement. He said he was amazed when Antram and Brown said the 
greens ``had suddenly become playable and the prime consideration 
was now the Golf Channel schedule.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I have no explanation of what transpired among the PGA  
officials between my Monday telephone conversation with Mr. Antram 
and the Wednesday meeting at the Hardscrabble Country Club,'' he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	He thanked the various sponsors and others and said officials  
would proceed with the same enthusiasm and vigor as they did last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Gosey said Tuesday that the Nike Tour is talking about the  
possibility of geographical realignment and that tournaments in 
this area of the country would either be earlier in the year or in 
the fall to avoid the heat and humidity. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
