<HEADLINE> Popson Retires With Head Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIVER FALLS, Wis. (AP) -- Tight end Ted Popson, who sustained  
head injuries twice last season, obeyed his doctor's orders and 
announced his retirement from the Kansas City Chiefs on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Popson, 32, played two years for the Chiefs after three with the  
San Francisco 49ers. He totaled 103 catches for 980 yards and eight 
touchdowns. 
</P>
