respect,'' said Chiefs' general manager Carl Peterson. ``I don't 
remember Ted Popson ever dropping a pass.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He was first injured in a savage tackle against Pittsburgh on a  
Monday night game in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	``That was about the most vicious hit I've ever seen in the  
NFL,'' said Peterson. ``But he held onto the ball.'' 
  	   	
