<DOCNO> APW19990805.0056 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 09:30:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> ITAR-Tass Establishes Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- The ITAR-Tass news agency announced today that it  
was establishing an annual journalism prize for the best Russian 
and international reporting from the Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
	The award will be known as the Posuvalyuk International  
Journalist Prize, named after Russian diplomat Viktor Posuvalyuk, a 
Middle East specialist who died Sunday, the news agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	Each year, one Russian and one non-Russian reporter will be  
awarded the prize by the news agency's board of directors. The 
winners will receive a diploma and a medal. 
</P>
<P>
	ITAR-Tass is the state-owned successor to the Soviet-era Tass  
news agency. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
