<HEADLINE> Toddler Attacked by Father's Python </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRUITLAND PARK, Fla. (AP) -- A 13-foot pet python almost killed  
an 18-month-old boy when it bit the child several times and wrapped 
itself around the child. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy's father was able to pry the 80-pound reptile from  
little Nickolas Graham and was bitten several times on both hands 
Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	An animal control officer caught the snake shortly after the  
attack and planned to destroy it. 
</P>
<P>
	Nickolas underwent plastic surgery to repair damage to his eye.  
</P>
<P>
	``I'm surprised the snake didn't kill the child,'' said Dave  
Bailey, a Lake County animal control officer. 
</P>
<P>
	The father, Bill Broyles, said he didn't know his pet had  
slithered outside near the concrete patio where Nickolas was 
playing. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want him dead,'' Broyles said of the snake, wringing his  
blood-covered hands. ``I don't want to see him again.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
