<HEADLINE> Rangers' Mateo Sidelined 6-8 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Texas center fielder Ruben Mateo was  
placed on the 15-day disabled list Thursday because of a broken 
left wrist, perhaps ending the rookie's season. 
</P>
<P>
	Mateo was injured while taking a swing in the eighth inning of  
Wednesday night's 3-1 win over Minnesota. Although preliminary 
X-rays appeared negative, further tests by a hand specialist 
revealed a fracture. 
</P>
<P>
	Mateo will undergo surgery to remove the broken bone Friday and  
is expected to be sidelined 6-8 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rangers will activate center fielder Tom Goodwin in time for  
Friday night's game against the Toronto Blue Jays. 
</P>
<P>
	Mateo, one of the Rangers' most highly touted prospects, is  
batting .238 with five homers and 18 RBIs in 32 games since his 
recall on June 12. He previously was on the disabled list from June 
23 to July 9 with a pulled groin muscle. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodwin is batting .241 with one homer, 12 RBIs and 27 stolen  
bases in 56 games this season. He has appeared in just one game 
since straining his left hip flexor muscle on June 11. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodwin came off the disabled list June 27, then returned to the  
DL the next day after aggravating the injury. 
</P>
<P>
	He recently completed a three-day medical rehabilitation  
assignment at Port Charlotte in the Florida State League, going 
4-for-10 in three starts in center. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
