<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Magic Johnson Goes on Tae-Bo Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- How does Magic Johnson stay fit?  
</P>
<P>
	He's been training with Tae-Bo creator Billy Blanks and was so  
impressed they've teamed up for a three-month fitness tour. 
</P>
<P>
	``Billy's been my personal trainer for a while now and his  
fantastic Tae-Bo workout has done great things for me,'' the former 
basketball legend said Wednesday. ``It helps keep me fit, 
energized, focused and positive.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tae Bo's combination of karate and boxing moves has become an  
American craze. Magic Johnson Productions is producing the 28-city 
tour starting Aug. 27 in Charlotte, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
	Blanks will run a two-hour Tae Bo workout that will include  
participation from the audience. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
