<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fox Baseball Ratings Up 11 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Halfway through its Saturday ``Game of the  
Week'' telecasts, Fox's ratings are up 11 percent this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox is averaging a 3.0 rating and 10 share for nine broadcasts,  
up 11 percent from its 2.7 rating for its first nine telecasts last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Last Saturday's regional telecasts averaged a 4.2 rating and 13  
share, Fox said Thursday. That was its second-highest Saturday 
since it began televising baseball in 1996, trailing only a 4.5 
rating and 14 share last Sept. 5, when Mark McGwire hit his 60th 
home run. 
</P>
<P>
	The rating is the percentage of television households tuned to a  
broadcast, and each point represents 994,000 homes. The share is 
the percentage watching a program among those televisions in use at 
the time. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox Sports Net's ratings for 16 Thursday night broadcasts are  
averaging an 0.91, up 18 percent from an 0.77 average in a similar 
period last season. 
</P>
<P>
	FX's ratings for 17 Saturday night telecasts are averaging an  
0.53, up 17 percent from a 0.47 average in a similar period last 
year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
