<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Carolina Trades Wilson to Green Bay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) -- The Carolina Panthers traded reserve  
offensive lineman Jamie Wilson to the Green Bay Packers today for 
an undisclosed draft choice. 
</P>
<P>
	Used as both a guard and tackle, the 6-foot-6, 300-pound Wilson  
played at Marshall before joining the Panthers as a free-agent 
rookie in 1997. He made Carolina's 53-man roster but didn't play in 
any games. 
</P>
<P>
	He injured a nerve in his neck in an exhibition game last  
August, underwent surgery and spent the entire 1998 season on 
injured reserve. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
