<HEADLINE> Cuba Sets Clean and Jerk Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) -- Hidalberto Aranda of Cuba set the  
world record in the clean and jerk for the 77 kilogram (division at 
the Pan American Games. Aranda lifted 205.5 kilograms (453 pounds) 
to break the record of 205.0 (452 pounds) set by Armenian Khachatur 
Kyapanaktsyan on Jan. 1, 1998 in La Coruna, Spain. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
