<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Spielberg Prepares Jurassic Park 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIVERSAL CITY, Calif. (AP) -- Are you ready for more dino-mania?  
</P>
<P>
	Steven Spielberg has hatched a storyline and Joe Johnston was  
picked to direct ``Jurassic Park 3.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Universal and Spielberg's Amblin Entertainment are shooting for  
an early 2000 production start. The script is being written by 
Craig Rosenberg in close collaboration with Johnston, who directed 
``Jumanji'' and ``October Sky.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Last year, Spielberg said he planned to direct the third  
installment, but he will be busy directing Tom Cruise in ``Minority 
Report.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The ``Jurassic Park'' dinosaur franchise has earned more than  
$1.5 billion in box office revenue. The original grossed $913 
million and the ``Lost World'' sequel earned more than $600 
million. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
