<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Young Campers Allege Marine Racism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Several black Washington area youths were  
subjected to racial taunts during a week-long military camp 
sponsored by the Marine Corps, according to The Washington Post. 
</P>
<P>
	Two dozen Washington area youths attended the Young Marines  
summer camp two weeks ago at Camp Lejeune, N.C. While there, one 
youth's mattress was ripped, his military boots were stolen and his 
wooden locker was covered with racial epithets scribbled in 
toothpaste, the newspaper said in its Thursday editions. 
</P>
<P>
	Another camper returned to his barracks and found a picture of  
his deceased parents torn and scattered on the floor, money and 
uniforms taken and the smell of stale urine in the air. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will never go back (to Camp Lejeune) for an encampment,''  
Leonard McFerson, commander of the Nation's Capitol Young Marines, 
told the Post. ``I try to get (youths) out of the city and show 
them something different, and if that's what they're going to see, 
I might as well let them run around the street and be gang 
members.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Maj. Dave Lapan, a spokesman for the U.S. Marine Corps -- which  
provides financial and logistical support to Young Marines but does 
not oversee the nonprofit group -- said, ``Incidents like that are 
certainly contrary to everything we believe in.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``We support the Young Marines' taking disciplinary action  
against those found accountable,'' Lapan said. 
</P>
<P>
	The two-week military camp features obstacles courses, drills  
and other activities aimed at fostering discipline, honesty and 
self-esteem in boys and girls ages 8 to 18. 
</P>
<P>
	Joseph Hall, a 15-year-old from Oxon Hill, Md., said the  
incidents made him feel ``violated.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Michael Kessler, the incoming national executive director of  
Young Marines, has launched an investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	``What I saw wasn't teasing, and that bothers me a lot,''  
Kessler said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
