<HEADLINE> Sullivan, Maple Leafs in 2-Year Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Forward Steve Sullivan, who had career highs in  
both goals scored and points last season, re-signed with the 
Toronto Maple Leafs on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sullivan signed a two-year deal worth $1.9 million. He will earn  
$825,000 this season and $1.07 million in 2000-2001. 
</P>
<P>
	Sullivan played in 63 games last season with Toronto, scoring 20  
and 40 points. He was one of six Maple Leafs to score 20 or more 
goals this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Sullivan has been in the NHL for five season. The Leafs acquired  
him in February, 1997 as part of a five-player deal with New Jersey 
in which the Devils acquired former Toronto captain Doug Gilmour. 
  	   	
</P>
