<HEADLINE> Sharpe May Miss Game in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Shannon Sharpe is having a bad week.  
</P>
<P>
	Already unhappy about traveling to Australia and dealing with  
its ``rude'' people, the Broncos tight end sprained his ankle 
during today's practice in Sydney. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury threatens to keep him out of Saturday night's game in  
Sydney against the San Diego Chargers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Regardless of whether I play or not, I'm still going to be  
hurt,'' Sharpe said as he walked off the practice field. 
</P>
<P>
	Broncos doctors examined both his knee and ankle and concluded  
Sharpe only had a sprained ankle. Broncos coach Mike Shanahan said 
he didn't think the injury was serious and would not require a 
magnetic resonance imaging test. 
</P>
<P>
	During his stay down under, Sharpe complained that people bumped  
into him and that he had to wait 20 minutes to get a cab. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm having a bad week, not just a bad day. I think today was  
really the icing on the cake,'' he said. 
  	   	
</P>
